Remediation Write-up for Acceptance Criteria #2 and #3

Remediation for Requirement #2 â€“ Ensure compliance with data-privacy regulations during user-data collection

Based on confirmation from the Product Owner and validation from the Glassbox team (email references attached), CRDP UI does not collect or display any PII/PHI/NPI/sensitive information that would require masking or additional protection before instrumentation.
Glassbox will only capture standard interaction-level events such as navigation paths, clicks, page views, and time spentâ€”none of which contain sensitive attributes or user-identifiable data.

Glassbox team has explicitly confirmed that:

All captured data is tied only to the userâ€™s BankID that is already authorized via application roles.

No masking is required because CRDP UI does not expose or transmit sensitive fields to Glassbox.

Access to Glassbox data is role-based and restricted to approved personas only.

Therefore, requirement #2 is fully satisfied through existing product design and Glassboxâ€™s role-controlled access model.

Remediation for Requirement #3 â€“ Provide real-time analytics dashboards with actionable insights

The real-time analytics capability for CRDP UI will be provided directly through the Glassbox Portal Dashboard, not through CRDP UI itself.
Once instrumentation is active for CRDP UI (AIT-72882), all analytics related to session behavior, user journeys, clicks, and heatmaps will automatically appear under the application profile in Glassbox.

To access these dashboards, users must:

Submit an ARM request to obtain appropriate analytics roles for Glassbox.

Select CRDP UI (AIT-72882) as the application they need access to.

Once approved, users will be able to view all real-time dashboards and insights through the Glassbox platform.

No additional development or UI integration on CRDP side is required for this functionality.

Therefore, requirement #3 is fulfilled through the Glassbox platformâ€™s native analytics capabilities, with access provisioned via ARM request workflow.

ðŸ”’ Final Consolidated Statement (Short Version for Jira)

Req #2: CRDP UI does not expose any sensitive data requiring protection prior to Glassbox ingestion. Glassbox team and PO have both confirmed no PII/PHI/NPI is involved. All data capture is limited to interaction-level metadata, and access is restricted via role-based Glassbox permissions.

Req #3: Real-time analytics dashboards are provided on the Glassbox portal. Users must raise an ARM request to obtain access to the analytics for AIT-72882. No CRDP UI changes are required.
